-- Colombian Stock Movers: Grupo Aval Declines; Ecopetrol Gains
-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 2011-12-21T17:17:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-21/colombian-stock-movers-grupo-aval-declines-ecopetrol-gains.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 11:44 a.m. local time.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  gained 0.1 percent to 12,659.15, while the
Colcap Index declined 0.2 percent to 1,577.05.  Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores SA (AVAL)  , Banco de
Bogota’s parent company, fell 2.5 percent to 1,190 pesos.  Colombian banks declined after Finance Minister Juan Carlos
Echeverry announced a new decree under which banks will be able
to charge a maximum 3,965 pesos for withdrawals from automated
teller machines outside their networks.  Ecopetrol SA (ECOPETL)  , Colombia’s largest oil company,
gained 0.4 percent to 4,235 pesos. Oil prices rose for a third
day as inventories declined the most in a decade.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
